PKN Orlen, KGHM, Gornictwo: Central European Stock Preview

-- B y   M a r t a   W a l d o c h
-- 
2011-04-11T04:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-10/pkn-orlen-kghm-gornictwo-central-european-stock-preview.html
The following is a list of
companies whose shares may have unusual price changes in central
European markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company
names. Share prices are from the April 8 close.  Poland ’s WIG20 Index fell 0.9 percent, the Czech PX Index
dropped 0.1 percent and  Hungary ’s BUX Index declined less than
0.1 percent.  PKN Orlen SA (PKN PW),  KGHM Polska Miedz SA (KGH)   and
PGE SA (PGE PW): Shareholders of Polkomtel SA, Poland’s second
largest mobile-phone operator, agreed the company will pay out
1.53 billion zloty, or 74.52 zloty a share, as dividend from
2010 net income, Polkomtel said in an e-mailed statement on
April 8. PKN rose 0.9 percent to 57 zloty, KGHM fell 0.3 percent
to 193.6 zloty and PGE added 1.1 percent to 23.25 zloty.  Polskie Gornictwo Naftowe i Gazownictwo SA (PGN)  : Poland
may deregulate gas prices for business consumers in two to three
years at the earliest, Rzeczpospolita newspaper reported on its
Rp.pl website, citing Maciej Kaliski, head of oil and gas at the
 Economy Ministry . The shares of Poland’s dominant gas company
dropped 1.3 percent to 3.78 zloty.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marta Waldoch in Warsaw on 
 mwaldoch@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Frank Connelly at   fconnelly@bloomberg.net  